{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":826,"text":"So I'd like you to imagine for a moment"},{"time":3493,"text":"that you're a soldier\nin the heat of battle."},{"time":6730,"text":"Maybe you're a Roman foot soldier\nor a medieval archer"},{"time":10285,"text":"or maybe you're a Zulu warrior."},{"time":12189,"text":"Regardless of your time and place,\nthere are some things that are constant."},{"time":16467,"text":"Your adrenaline is elevated,"},{"time":18385,"text":"and your actions are stemming\nfrom these deeply ingrained reflexes,"},{"time":23218,"text":"reflexes rooted in a need\nto protect yourself and your side"},{"time":27598,"text":"and to defeat the enemy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":30826,"text":"So now, I'd like you to imagine\nplaying a very different role,"},{"time":34387,"text":"that of the scout."},{"time":36012,"text":"The scout's job is not\nto attack or defend."},{"time":39425,"text":"The scout's job is to understand."},{"time":42233,"text":"The scout is the one going out,"},{"time":44318,"text":"mapping the terrain,\nidentifying potential obstacles."},{"time":48405,"text":"And the scout may hope to learn\nthat, say, there's a bridge"},{"time":52005,"text":"in a convenient location across a river."},{"time":54363,"text":"But above all, the scout\nwants to know what's really there,"},{"time":57434,"text":"as accurately as possible."},{"time":60195,"text":"And in a real, actual army, both\nthe soldier and the scout are essential."},{"time":65265,"text":"But you can also think of each\nof these roles as a mindset --"},{"time":70599,"text":"a metaphor for how all of us\nprocess information and ideas"},{"time":74250,"text":"in our daily lives."},{"time":76192,"text":"What I'm going to argue today\nis that having good judgment,"},{"time":80046,"text":"making accurate predictions,\nmaking good decisions,"},{"time":83284,"text":"is mostly about which mindset you're in."}]},{"cues":[{"time":86994,"text":"To illustrate these mindsets in action,"},{"time":89611,"text":"I'm going to take you back\nto 19th-century France,"},{"time":93119,"text":"where this innocuous-looking\npiece of paper"},{"time":96126,"text":"launched one of the biggest\npolitical scandals in history."},{"time":99718,"text":"It was discovered in 1894\nby officers in the French general staff."},{"time":104616,"text":"It was torn up in a wastepaper basket,"},{"time":107332,"text":"but when they pieced it back together,"},{"time":109281,"text":"they discovered\nthat someone in their ranks"},{"time":111337,"text":"had been selling\nmilitary secrets to Germany."}]},{"cues":[{"time":114462,"text":"So they launched a big investigation,"},{"time":116843,"text":"and their suspicions\nquickly converged on this man,"},{"time":120733,"text":"Alfred Dreyfus."},{"time":122867,"text":"He had a sterling record,"},{"time":124209,"text":"no past history of wrongdoing,\nno motive as far as they could tell."},{"time":128342,"text":"But Dreyfus was the only\nJewish officer at that rank in the army,"},{"time":133484,"text":"and unfortunately at this time,\nthe French Army was highly anti-Semitic."},{"time":137683,"text":"They compared Dreyfus's handwriting\nto that on the memo"},{"time":140929,"text":"and concluded that it was a match,"},{"time":142890,"text":"even though outside\nprofessional handwriting experts"},{"time":145956,"text":"were much less confident\nin the similarity,"},{"time":148130,"text":"but never mind that."},{"time":149544,"text":"They went and searched\nDreyfus's apartment,"},{"time":151608,"text":"looking for any signs of espionage."},{"time":153388,"text":"They went through his files,\nand they didn't find anything."},{"time":156372,"text":"This just convinced them more\nthat Dreyfus was not only guilty,"},{"time":159530,"text":"but sneaky as well, because clearly\nhe had hidden all of the evidence"},{"time":162847,"text":"before they had managed to get to it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":165212,"text":"Next, they went and looked\nthrough his personal history"},{"time":167928,"text":"for any incriminating details."},{"time":170253,"text":"They talked to his teachers,"},{"time":171879,"text":"they found that he had studied\nforeign languages in school,"},{"time":174688,"text":"which clearly showed a desire\nto conspire with foreign governments"},{"time":178765,"text":"later in life."},{"time":179972,"text":"His teachers also said that Dreyfus\nwas known for having a good memory,"},{"time":186007,"text":"which was highly suspicious, right?"},{"time":188143,"text":"You know, because a spy\nhas to remember a lot of things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":192439,"text":"So the case went to trial,\nand Dreyfus was found guilty."},{"time":196816,"text":"Afterwards, they took him out\ninto this public square"},{"time":200160,"text":"and ritualistically tore\nhis insignia from his uniform"},{"time":203908,"text":"and broke his sword in two."},{"time":205837,"text":"This was called\nthe Degradation of Dreyfus."},{"time":208860,"text":"And they sentenced him\nto life imprisonment"},{"time":211401,"text":"on the aptly named Devil's Island,"},{"time":214165,"text":"which is this barren rock\noff the coast of South America."},{"time":217556,"text":"So there he went,\nand there he spent his days alone,"},{"time":221330,"text":"writing letters and letters\nto the French government"},{"time":223858,"text":"begging them to reopen his case\nso they could discover his innocence."},{"time":227634,"text":"But for the most part,\nFrance considered the matter closed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":231301,"text":"One thing that's really interesting\nto me about the Dreyfus Affair"},{"time":235618,"text":"is this question of why the officers\nwere so convinced"},{"time":239420,"text":"that Dreyfus was guilty."},{"time":241556,"text":"I mean, you might even assume\nthat they were setting him up,"},{"time":244427,"text":"that they were intentionally framing him."},{"time":246419,"text":"But historians don't think\nthat's what happened."},{"time":248710,"text":"As far as we can tell,"},{"time":249893,"text":"the officers genuinely believed\nthat the case against Dreyfus was strong."},{"time":254154,"text":"Which makes you wonder:"},{"time":256654,"text":"What does it say about the human mind"},{"time":258952,"text":"that we can find such paltry evidence"},{"time":261289,"text":"to be compelling enough to convict a man?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":264210,"text":"Well, this is a case of what scientists\ncall \"motivated reasoning.\""},{"time":268520,"text":"It's this phenomenon in which\nour unconscious motivations,"},{"time":271598,"text":"our desires and fears,"},{"time":273974,"text":"shape the way we interpret information."},{"time":276344,"text":"Some information, some ideas,\nfeel like our allies."},{"time":279778,"text":"We want them to win.\nWe want to defend them."},{"time":282444,"text":"And other information\nor ideas are the enemy,"},{"time":284999,"text":"and we want to shoot them down."},{"time":287408,"text":"So this is why I call\nmotivated reasoning, \"soldier mindset.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":291988,"text":"Probably most of you have never persecuted"},{"time":295017,"text":"a French-Jewish officer for high treason,"},{"time":297322,"text":"I assume,"},{"time":298819,"text":"but maybe you've followed sports\nor politics, so you might have noticed"},{"time":303702,"text":"that when the referee judges\nthat your team committed a foul,"},{"time":307848,"text":"for example,"},{"time":309034,"text":"you're highly motivated\nto find reasons why he's wrong."},{"time":312482,"text":"But if he judges that the other team\ncommitted a foul -- awesome!"},{"time":315618,"text":"That's a good call,\nlet's not examine it too closely."},{"time":318792,"text":"Or, maybe you've read\nan article or a study"},{"time":320933,"text":"that examined some controversial policy,"},{"time":323663,"text":"like capital punishment."},{"time":325735,"text":"And, as researchers have demonstrated,"},{"time":327876,"text":"if you support capital punishment"},{"time":329605,"text":"and the study shows\nthat it's not effective,"},{"time":332145,"text":"then you're highly motivated\nto find all the reasons"},{"time":335415,"text":"why the study was poorly designed."},{"time":337612,"text":"But if it shows\nthat capital punishment works,"},{"time":339842,"text":"it's a good study."},{"time":341025,"text":"And vice versa: if you don't\nsupport capital punishment, same thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":344297,"text":"Our judgment is strongly\ninfluenced, unconsciously,"},{"time":347150,"text":"by which side we want to win."},{"time":350071,"text":"And this is ubiquitous."},{"time":351984,"text":"This shapes how we think\nabout our health, our relationships,"},{"time":355046,"text":"how we decide how to vote,"},{"time":356966,"text":"what we consider fair or ethical."},{"time":360036,"text":"What's most scary to me\nabout motivated reasoning"},{"time":362823,"text":"or soldier mindset,"},{"time":363998,"text":"is how unconscious it is."},{"time":365269,"text":"We can think we're being\nobjective and fair-minded"},{"time":368573,"text":"and still wind up ruining the life\nof an innocent man."}]},{"cues":[{"time":373008,"text":"However, fortunately for Dreyfus,\nhis story is not over."},{"time":375915,"text":"This is Colonel Picquart."},{"time":377307,"text":"He's another high-ranking officer\nin the French Army,"},{"time":379875,"text":"and like most people,\nhe assumed Dreyfus was guilty."},{"time":382893,"text":"Also like most people in the army,\nhe was at least casually anti-Semitic."},{"time":387342,"text":"But at a certain point,\nPicquart began to suspect:"},{"time":391302,"text":"\"What if we're all wrong about Dreyfus?\""},{"time":394448,"text":"What happened was,\nhe had discovered evidence"},{"time":396650,"text":"that the spying for Germany had continued,"},{"time":399151,"text":"even after Dreyfus was in prison."},{"time":401516,"text":"And he had also discovered\nthat another officer in the army"},{"time":404836,"text":"had handwriting that perfectly\nmatched the memo,"},{"time":407433,"text":"much closer than Dreyfus's handwriting."},{"time":410382,"text":"So he brought these discoveries\nto his superiors,"},{"time":414017,"text":"but to his dismay,\nthey either didn't care"},{"time":417718,"text":"or came up with elaborate rationalizations\nto explain his findings,"},{"time":421330,"text":"like, \"Well, all you've really shown,\nPicquart, is that there's another spy"},{"time":426727,"text":"who learned how to mimic\nDreyfus's handwriting,"},{"time":429124,"text":"and he picked up the torch of spying\nafter Dreyfus left."},{"time":433148,"text":"But Dreyfus is still guilty.\""},{"time":435854,"text":"Eventually, Picquart managed\nto get Dreyfus exonerated."},{"time":438903,"text":"But it took him 10 years,"},{"time":440455,"text":"and for part of that time,\nhe himself was in prison"},{"time":443010,"text":"for the crime of disloyalty to the army."}]},{"cues":[{"time":446491,"text":"A lot of people feel like Picquart\ncan't really be the hero of this story"},{"time":452515,"text":"because he was an anti-Semite\nand that's bad, which I agree with."},{"time":457323,"text":"But personally, for me,\nthe fact that Picquart was anti-Semitic"},{"time":461998,"text":"actually makes his actions more admirable,"},{"time":464607,"text":"because he had the same prejudices,\nthe same reasons to be biased"},{"time":467747,"text":"as his fellow officers,"},{"time":469556,"text":"but his motivation to find the truth\nand uphold it trumped all of that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":475108,"text":"So to me,"},{"time":476321,"text":"Picquart is a poster child\nfor what I call \"scout mindset.\""},{"time":480598,"text":"It's the drive not to make\none idea win or another lose,"},{"time":484698,"text":"but just to see what's really there"},{"time":486646,"text":"as honestly and accurately as you can,"},{"time":489145,"text":"even if it's not pretty\nor convenient or pleasant."},{"time":493444,"text":"This mindset is what\nI'm personally passionate about."},{"time":496714,"text":"And I've spent the last few years\nexamining and trying to figure out"},{"time":501867,"text":"what causes scout mindset."},{"time":503874,"text":"Why are some people, sometimes at least,"},{"time":507046,"text":"able to cut through their own prejudices\nand biases and motivations"},{"time":510858,"text":"and just try to see the facts\nand the evidence"},{"time":513177,"text":"as objectively as they can?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":515602,"text":"And the answer is emotional."},{"time":519119,"text":"So, just as soldier mindset\nis rooted in emotions"},{"time":522910,"text":"like defensiveness or tribalism,"},{"time":526615,"text":"scout mindset is, too."},{"time":528005,"text":"It's just rooted in different emotions."},{"time":530015,"text":"For example, scouts are curious."},{"time":533458,"text":"They're more likely to say\nthey feel pleasure"},{"time":537028,"text":"when they learn new information"},{"time":538712,"text":"or an itch to solve a puzzle."},{"time":541544,"text":"They're more likely to feel intrigued\nwhen they encounter something"},{"time":544737,"text":"that contradicts their expectations."},{"time":547206,"text":"Scouts also have different values."},{"time":549207,"text":"They're more likely to say\nthey think it's virtuous"},{"time":552303,"text":"to test your own beliefs,"},{"time":553816,"text":"and they're less likely to say\nthat someone who changes his mind"},{"time":557546,"text":"seems weak."},{"time":558832,"text":"And above all, scouts are grounded,"},{"time":560741,"text":"which means their self-worth as a person"},{"time":564670,"text":"isn't tied to how right or wrong\nthey are about any particular topic."},{"time":570160,"text":"So they can believe\nthat capital punishment works."},{"time":573438,"text":"If studies come out showing\nthat it doesn't, they can say,"},{"time":576275,"text":"\"Huh. Looks like I might be wrong.\nDoesn't mean I'm bad or stupid.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":581954,"text":"This cluster of traits\nis what researchers have found --"},{"time":586304,"text":"and I've also found anecdotally --"},{"time":588034,"text":"predicts good judgment."},{"time":590386,"text":"And the key takeaway I want\nto leave you with about those traits"},{"time":593693,"text":"is that they're primarily\nnot about how smart you are"},{"time":597354,"text":"or about how much you know."},{"time":599376,"text":"In fact, they don't correlate\nvery much with IQ at all."},{"time":602638,"text":"They're about how you feel."},{"time":604849,"text":"There's a quote that I keep\ncoming back to, by Saint-Exupéry."},{"time":608896,"text":"He's the author of \"The Little Prince.\""},{"time":610861,"text":"He said, \"If you want to build a ship,"},{"time":614234,"text":"don't drum up your men\nto collect wood and give orders"},{"time":618879,"text":"and distribute the work."},{"time":620669,"text":"Instead, teach them to yearn\nfor the vast and endless sea.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":626252,"text":"In other words, I claim,"},{"time":628850,"text":"if we really want to improve\nour judgment as individuals"},{"time":632034,"text":"and as societies,"},{"time":633501,"text":"what we need most\nis not more instruction in logic"},{"time":637034,"text":"or rhetoric or probability or economics,"},{"time":640606,"text":"even though those things\nare quite valuable."},{"time":642713,"text":"But what we most need\nto use those principles well"},{"time":646041,"text":"is scout mindset."},{"time":647483,"text":"We need to change the way we feel."},{"time":649759,"text":"We need to learn how to feel proud\ninstead of ashamed"},{"time":653593,"text":"when we notice we might\nhave been wrong about something."},{"time":656255,"text":"We need to learn how to feel intrigued\ninstead of defensive"},{"time":659407,"text":"when we encounter some information\nthat contradicts our beliefs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":664555,"text":"So the question I want\nto leave you with is:"},{"time":667817,"text":"What do you most yearn for?"},{"time":670771,"text":"Do you yearn to defend your own beliefs?"},{"time":674128,"text":"Or do you yearn to see the world\nas clearly as you possibly can?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":678352,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":679527,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}